<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 04 at 8:43PM MDT  by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of western Judith
Basin, south central Chouteau and southeastern Cascade Counties
through 930 PM MDT...
At 842 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 11 miles southwest of Geraldine to 12 miles
southwest of Geyser. Movement was east northeast at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Geraldine, Geyser, Neihart, Raynesford, Square Butte and Monarch.
This includes the following highways...
Highway 200 between mile markers 5 and 31.
Highway 89 between mile markers 29 and 59.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
